name: state_number
description: This data element identifies the state in which the crash occurred. The codes are from the General Services Administration’s (GSA) publication of worldwide Geographic Location Codes (GLC). For more info on the codes, please look at <C1/V1/D1/PC1/P1/NM1 State Number> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: state_name
description: This data element identifies the state in which the crash occurred. The codes are from the General Services Administration’s (GSA) publication of worldwide Geographic Location Codes (GLC).

name: consecutive_number
description: This data element is the unique case number assigned to each crash. It appears on each data file and is used to merge information from the data files together. xxxxxx Two Characters for State Code followed by Four Characters for Case Number

name: number_of_vehicle_forms_submitted_all
description: number_of_vehicle_forms_submitted_all

name: number_of_motor_vehicles_in_transport_mvit
description: This data element is a count of the number of vehicles in-transport involved in the crash. Legally parked vehicles are not included. 001-999 Number of Vehicle Forms

name: number_of_parked_working_vehicles
description: This data element is a count of the number of parked and working vehicles involved in the crash. 0-999 Number of Parked/Working Vehicles in the Crash

name: number_of_forms_submitted_for_persons_not_in_motor_vehicles
description: This data element is the number of Person Forms (Not a Motor Vehicle Occupant) that are applicable to this case (i.e., non-occupants). 00-99 Number of Persons Not in Motor Vehicles

name: number_of_forms_submitted_for_persons_in_motor_vehicles
description: This data element is a count of the number of Person Level (Motor Vehicle Occupant) Forms that are applicable to this case (i.e., occupants). 000-999 Number of Person Forms

name: number_of_persons_in_motor_vehicles_in_transport_mvit
description: This data element is a count of the number of motorists in the crash. A motorist is a driver, passenger or unknown occupant type of a motor vehicle in-transport. 0-999 Number of Persons in Motor Vehicles In-Transport

name: number_of_persons_not_in_motor_vehicles_in_transport_mvit
description: This data element is a count of the number of non-motorists in the crash. A non-motorist is defined as a pedestrian, a cyclist, an occupant of a motor vehicle not intransport, a person riding a horse, an occupant of an animal drawn conveyance, person associated with non-motorist conveyance (e.g., baby carriage, skate board, wheelchair), or an other non-motorist (e.g., person outside a trafficway, person in a house). 0-98 Number of Persons Not in Motor Vehicles in Transport

name: county
description: This data element records the location of the unstabilized event with regard to the County. The codes are from the General Services Administration’s (GSA) publication of worldwide Geographic Location Codes (GLC). 000 Not Applicable 001-996 Use GSA Geographical Codes 997 Other 998 Not Reported 999 Unknown

name: city
description: This data element records the location of the unstabilized event with regard to the City. The codes are from the General Services Administration’s (GSA) publication of worldwide Geographic Location Codes (GLC). 0000 Not Applicable 0001-9996 GSA Geographical Codes 9997 Other 9898 Not Reported 9999 Unknown

name: day_of_crash
description: This data element records the day of the month on which the crash occurred. 01-31 Day of the Month of the Crash -- Unknown

name: day_name
description: This data element records the day of the month on which the crash occurred. 01-31 Day of the Month of the Crash -- Unknown

name: month_of_crash
description: This data element records the month in which the crash occurred. For more info on the codes, please look at <C8A Month of Crash> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: month_of_crash_name
description: This data element records the month in which the crash occurred. For more info on the codes, please look at <C8A Month of Crash> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: year_of_crash
description: This data element records the year in which the crash occurred. xxxx Year of the Crash

name: day_of_week
description: This data element records the day of the week on which the crash occurred. 1 Sunday 2 Monday 3 Tuesday 4 Wednesday 5 Thursday 6 Friday 7 Saturday -- Unknown

name: day_of_week_name
description: This data element records the day of the week on which the crash occurred. 1 Sunday 2 Monday 3 Tuesday 4 Wednesday 5 Thursday 6 Friday 7 Saturday -- Unknown

name: hour_of_crash
description: This data element records the hour at which the crash occurred. 00-23 Hour -- Not Applicable or Not Notified 99 Unknown

name: hour_of_crash_name
description: This data element records the hour at which the crash occurred. 00-23 Hour -- Not Applicable or Not Notified 99 Unknown

name: minute_of_crash
description: This data element records the minutes after the hour at which the crash occurred. 00-59 Minute -- Not Applicable or Not Notified 99 Unknown

name: minute_of_crash_name
description: This data element records the minutes after the hour at which the crash occurred. 00-59 Minute -- Not Applicable or Not Notified 99 Unknown

name: national_highway_system
description: This data element identifies whether this crash occurred on a trafficway that is part of the National Highway System. 0 This Section is Not on the National Highway System 1 This Section is on the National Highway System 9 Unknown

name: national_highway_system_name
description: This data element identifies whether this crash occurred on a trafficway that is part of the National Highway System. 0 This Section is Not on the National Highway System 1 This Section is on the National Highway System 9 Unknown

name: route_signing
description: This data element identifies the route signing of the trafficway on which the crash occurred. 1 Interstate 2 U.S. Highway 3 State Highway 4 County Road 5 Local Street – Township 6 Local Street – Municipality 7 Local Street – Frontage Road (Since 1994) 8 Other 9 Unknown

name: route_signing_name
description: This data element identifies the route signing of the trafficway on which the crash occurred.

name: trafficway_identifier
description: This data element records the trafficway on which the crash occurred. xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx Actual Posted Number, Assigned Number, or Common Name (30 characters) 999999999999999999999999999999 Unknown

name: trafficway_identifier_2
description: This data element records the trafficway on which the crash occurred. xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx Actual Posted Number, Assigned Number, or Common Name (30 characters) 999999999999999999999999999999 Unknown

name: land_use
description: 1 (Rural), 2 (Urban), 6 (Trafficway Not in State Inventory), 8 (Not Reported) and 9 (Unknown).

name: land_use_name
description: 1 (Rural), 2 (Urban), 6 (Trafficway Not in State Inventory), 8 (Not Reported) and 9 (Unknown).

name: functional_system
description: 01 (Interstate), 02 (Principal Arterial – Other Freeways and Expressways), 03 (Principal Arterial – Other), 04 (Minor Arterial), 05 (Major Collector), 06 (Minor Collector), 07 (Local), 96 (Trafficway Not in State Inventory), 98 (Not Reported), and 99 (Unknown).

name: functional_system_name
description: 01 (Interstate), 02 (Principal Arterial – Other Freeways and Expressways), 03 (Principal Arterial – Other), 04 (Minor Arterial), 05 (Major Collector), 06 (Minor Collector), 07 (Local), 96 (Trafficway Not in State Inventory), 98 (Not Reported), and 99 (Unknown).

name: ownership
description: For more info on the codes, please look at <C13 Ownership> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: ownership_name
description: For more info on the codes, please look at <C13 Ownership> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: milepoint
description: This data element records the milepoint nearest to the location where the crash occurred. 00000 None xxxxx Actual to Nearest Tenth Mile (Assume decimal, e.g., 12345 = 1234.5) 99998 Not Reported 99999 Unknown

name: milepoint_name
description: This data element records the milepoint nearest to the location where the crash occurred. 00000 None xxxxx Actual to Nearest Tenth Mile (Assume decimal, e.g., 12345 = 1234.5) 99998 Not Reported 99999 Unknown

name: latitude
description: This element identifies the location of the crash using Global Position coordinates. This is the position of latitude. DDDDDD (DD.DDDD – Decimal Degrees) DD.DDDD Actual Degrees 77.7777 Not Reported 88.8888 Not Available (If State Exempt) 99.9999 Unknown

name: latitude_name
description: This element identifies the location of the crash using Global Position coordinates. This is the position of latitude. DDDDDD (DD.DDDD – Decimal Degrees) DD.DDDD Actual Degrees 77.7777 Not Reported 88.8888 Not Available (If State Exempt) 99.9999 Unknown

name: longitude
description: This element identifies the location of the crash using Global Position coordinates. This is the position of longitude. DDDDDDD (DDD.DDDD – Decimal Degrees) DDD.DDDD Actual Degrees 777.7777 Not Reported 888.8888 Not Available (If State Exempt) 999.9999 Unknown

name: longitude_name
description: This element identifies the location of the crash using Global Position coordinates. This is the position of longitude. DDDDDDD (DDD.DDDD – Decimal Degrees) DDD.DDDD Actual Degrees 777.7777 Not Reported 888.8888 Not Available (If State Exempt) 999.9999 Unknown

name: special_jurisdiction
description: This data element identifies if the location on the trafficway where the crash occurred qualifies as a Special Jurisdiction even though it may be patrolled by state, county or local police (e.g., all State highways running through Indian reservations are under the jurisdiction of the Indian reservation). 0 No Special Jurisdiction (Includes National Forests Since 2008) 1 National Park Service 2 Military 3 Indian Reservation 4 College/University Campus 5 Other Federal Properties (Since 1977) 8 Other (Since 1976) 9 Unknown

name: special_jurisdiction_name
description: This data element identifies if the location on the trafficway where the crash occurred qualifies as a Special Jurisdiction even though it may be patrolled by state, county or local police (e.g., all State highways running through Indian reservations are under the jurisdiction of the Indian reservation).

name: first_harmful_event
description: This data element describes the first injury or damage producing event of the crash. For more info on the codes, please look at <C19 First Harmful Event> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: first_harmful_event_name
description: This data element describes the first injury or damage producing event of the crash.

name: manner_of_collision
description: This data element describes the orientation of two motor vehicles in-transport when they are involved in the “First Harmful Event” of a collision crash. If the “First Harmful Event” is not a collision between two motor vehicles in-transport it is classified as such. For more info on the codes, please look at <C20 Manner of Collision> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: manner_of_collision_name
description: This data element describes the orientation of two motor vehicles in-transport when they are involved in the “First Harmful Event” of a collision crash. If the “First Harmful Event” is not a collision between two motor vehicles in-transport it is classified as such.

name: relation_to_junction_within_interchange_area
description: This data element identifies the crash's location with respect to presence in an interchange area. The coding of this data element is done in two sub-fields (see also C20B) and is based on the location of the “First Harmful Event” of the crash. 0 No 1 Yes 8 Not Reported 9 Unknown

name: relation_to_junction_within_interchange_area_name
description: This data element identifies the crash's location with respect to presence in an interchange area. The coding of this data element is done in two sub-fields (see also C20B) and is based on the location of the “First Harmful Event” of the crash. 0 No 1 Yes 8 Not Reported 9 Unknown

name: relation_to_junction_specific_location
description: This data element identifies the crash's location with respect to presence in or proximity to components typically in junction or interchange areas. The coding of this data element is done in two sub-fields (see also C20A) and is based on the location of the “First Harmful Event” of the crash. For more info on the codes, please look at <C21B Relation to Junction- Specific Location> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: relation_to_junction_specific_location_name
description: This data element identifies the crash's location with respect to presence in or proximity to components typically in junction or interchange areas. The coding of this data element is done in two sub-fields (see also C20A) and is based on the location of the “First Harmful Event” of the crash.

name: type_of_intersection
description: This data element identifies and allows separation of various intersection types. 1 Not an Intersection 2 Four-Way Intersection 3 T-Intersection 4 Y-Intersection 5 Traffic Circle 6 Roundabout 7 Five-Point, or More 10 L-Intersection 98 Not Reported 99 Unknown

name: type_of_intersection_name
description: This data element identifies and allows separation of various intersection types. 1 Not an Intersection 2 Four-Way Intersection 3 T-Intersection 4 Y-Intersection 5 Traffic Circle 6 Roundabout 7 Five-Point, or More 10 L-Intersection 98 Not Reported 99 Unknown

name: work_zone
description: This data element identifies a motor vehicle traffic crash in which the first harmful event occurs within the boundaries of a work zone or on an approach to or exit from a work zone, resulting from an activity, behavior, or control related to the movement of the traffic units through the work zone. 0 None 1 Construction 2 Maintenance -- Construction or Maintenance 3 Utility 4 Work Zone, Type Unknown -- Not Reported

name: work_zone_name
description: This data element identifies a motor vehicle traffic crash in which the first harmful event occurs within the boundaries of a work zone or on an approach to or exit from a work zone, resulting from an activity, behavior, or control related to the movement of the traffic units through the work zone. 0 None 1 Construction 2 Maintenance -- Construction or Maintenance 3 Utility 4 Work Zone, Type Unknown -- Not Reported

name: relation_to_trafficway
description: This data element identifies the location of the crash as it relates to its position within or outside the trafficway based on the “First Harmful Event.” For more info on the codes, please look at <C23 Relation to Trafficway> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: relation_to_trafficway_name
description: This data element identifies the location of the crash as it relates to its position within or outside the trafficway based on the “First Harmful Event.”

name: light_condition
description: This data element records the type/level of light that existed at the time of the crash as indicated in the case material. For more info on the codes, please look at <C25 Light Condition> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: light_condition_name
description: This data element records the type/level of light that existed at the time of the crash as indicated in the case material.

name: atmospheric_conditions_1
description: This data element records the prevailing atmospheric conditions that existed at the time of the crash as indicated in the case material. For more info on the codes, please look at <C26 Atmospheric Conditions> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: atmospheric_conditions_1_name
description: This data element records the prevailing atmospheric conditions that existed at the time of the crash as indicated in the case material.

name: atmospheric_conditions_2

name: atmospheric_conditions_2_name
description: This data element records the prevailing atmospheric conditions that existed at the time of the crash as indicated in the case material.

name: atmospheric_conditions
description: This data element records the prevailing atmospheric conditions that existed at the time of the crash as indicated in the case material. For more info on the codes, please look at <C26 Atmospheric Conditions> section in the pdf: https://crashstats.nhtsa.dot.gov/Api/Public/ViewPublication/812315

name: school_bus_related
description: This data element identifies if a school bus, or motor vehicle functioning as a school bus, is related to the crash. 0 No 1 Yes -- Not Reported

name: school_bus_related_name
description: This data element identifies if a school bus, or motor vehicle functioning as a school bus, is related to the crash. 0 No 1 Yes -- Not Reported

name: rail_grade_crossing_identifier
description: This data element identifies if the crash occurred in or near a rail grade crossing. 0000000 Not Applicable xxxxxxA Six Digits Followed by One Alphabetic Valid F.R.A. Code 9999999 Unknown

name: rail_grade_crossing_identifier_name
description: This data element identifies if the crash occurred in or near a rail grade crossing. 0000000 Not Applicable xxxxxxA Six Digits Followed by One Alphabetic Valid F.R.A. Code 9999999 Unknown

name: hour_of_notification
description: This data element records the hour that emergency medical service was notified. 00-23 Hour -- Not Applicable or Not Notified (when NOT_MIN = 00) 88 Not Applicable or Not Notified 99 Unknown Hour 99 Unknown if Notified (when NOT_MIN = 98)

name: hour_of_notification_name

name: minute_of_notification
description: This data element records the minutes after the hour that emergency medical service was notified. 00-59 Minute -- Not Applicable or Not Notified (when NOT_HOUR = 00) 88 Not Applicable or Not Notified 98 Unknown if Notified 99 Unknown Minutes

name: minute_of_notification_name
description: This data element records the minutes after the hour that emergency medical service was notified. 00-59 Minute -- Not Applicable or Not Notified (when NOT_HOUR = 00) 88 Not Applicable or Not Notified 98 Unknown if Notified 99 Unknown Minutes

name: hour_of_arrival_at_scene
description: This data element records the hour that emergency medical service arrived on the crash scene. 00-23 Hour -- Not Notified or Officially Cancelled (when ARR_MIN = 00) -- Not Notified (when ARR_MIN = 00) 88 Not Applicable or Not Notified 99 Unknown Hour 99 Officially Cancelled (when ARR_MIN = 97) 99 Unknown if Arrived (when ARR_MIN = 98)

name: hour_of_arrival_at_scene_name

name: minute_of_arrival_at_scene

name: hour_of_ems_arrival_at_hospital

name: minute_of_ems_arrival_at_hospital
description: This data element records the minutes after the hour that emergency medical service arrived at the treatment facility to which it was transporting victims of the crash. 00-59 Minute -- Not Notified, Officially Cancelled or Not Transported (when HOSP_HR = 00) -- Not Notified or Not Transported (when HOSP_HR = 00) 88 Not Applicable or Not Notified 96 Terminated Transport 97 Officially Cancelled 98 Unknown if Transported 99 Unknown Minutes
